Introduction

Saturday is a three-member South Korean girl group under Yoonso Group. They originally debuted as a seven-member group with the single "MMook JJi BBa" on July 18th, 2018, under the now-defunct company SD Entertainment.

On December 1st, 2018, less than a year after their debut, Chaewon left the group to focus on her studies. Juyeon was added to the group on January 22nd, 2019, to retain the group's seven-member lineup.

On February 13th, 2019, Saturday had their first comeback with the single album "Follow SATURDAY." Saturday would undergo three more lineup changes in 2019, with Sunha leaving on March 29th, Minseo being introduced as a new member on April 13th. and the announcement of Sion and Chohee's departures on August 22nd. The remaining five members released their third single "IYKYK" on September 19th, 2019.

Saturday promoted as a five-member group for two more singles: "D.B.D.B.DIB", released August 3rd, 2020, and "Only You", released January 22nd, 2021.

In 2022, SD Entertainment's building was found to be abandoned, sparking concern about Saturday's status amongst fans. However, the group was presumably transferred to Yoonso Group sometime in 2023. On July 18th, 2023, Yoonso Group announced that Saturday would be having their first comeback in over two years, but that Saturday would be continuing with only four members due to Haneul's departure. They made their comeback with "Find Summer" on July 25th, 2023.
